{{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Theodore_Beza" }}{\fldrslt{\ul\cf1\cf1\ul Wikipedia}}}}\f0\fs20\par\
\cf2\b Theodore Beza\b0  (Latin \b Theodorus Beza\b0 , French \b Th\'e9odore de B\'e8ze\b0  or \b de Besze\b0 ) (June 24, 1519 \endash  October 13, 1605) was a \cf0 French\cf2  \cf0 Protestant Christian\cf2  \cf0 theologian\cf2  and \cf0 scholar\cf2  who played an important role in the \cf0 Reformation\cf2 . A member of the \cf0 monarchomaque\cf2  movement who opposed \cf0 absolute monarchy\cf2 , he was a disciple of \cf0 John Calvin\cf2  and lived most of his life in Switzerland.\par\
\f1\fs28\par\
\
\pard\cf0\f2\fs24\par\
